# Vocabulary lookup uses only free, offline-friendly sources (bundled WordNet + the community
# Free Dictionary API + CC-CEDICT) and needs NO API keys. This file documents the optional
# server settings; copy it to .env only if you want to override a default.

# HOST=127.0.0.1
# PORT=3000
# LOG_LEVEL=info
# DATABASE_DIR=
# The `dev` script persists to a git-ignored .data/db by default; `start` is in-memory. Set
# DATABASE_DIR to a path to choose your own location, or "" to force in-memory under `dev`.
# SOURCE_FILES_DIR=./.data/sources
# EPUB_UPLOAD_LIMIT_BYTES=52428800
# WEB_DIR=
# Single-origin deploy (see docs/DEPLOY.md): set WEB_DIR to the built web client
# (src/apps/web/dist) and the server also serves the app at `/` alongside `/api/*`. Unset in dev,
# where Vite serves the client separately.

# COACH_API_KEY=
# Cloud key for the coach's strong tier (the end-of-round judge). Unset = coach runs entirely on the
# deterministic fake. With a key set, defaults give local converse (Ollama llama3.1:8b) + cloud judge.
# See docs/COACH.md to install Ollama and pull the model. Never commit a real key.
# COACH_CONVERSE_TIER=cheap
# COACH_ANALYZE_TIER=strong
# Per-call tier overrides (cheap = local Ollama, strong = cloud). Defaults already match these.

# WHISPER_BINARY=
# WHISPER_MODEL_PATH=
# WHISPER_LANGUAGE=
# Local Whisper STT for spoken practice (see docs/SPEECH.md). Both WHISPER_BINARY (the whisper CLI /
# wrapper launcher) and WHISPER_MODEL_PATH (a faster-whisper model size like `small`/`base.en`, or a
# path) must be set to enable it; WHISPER_LANGUAGE (default `en`) is optional. Unset = spoken practice
# transcribes to empty. The easiest way to fill these in is `pnpm setup --voice`, which installs the
# wrapper, fetches the model, and writes these three values here.
